Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.10,0:00:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you really spruce up\Nthe office, Ms. Philodendron.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.21,0:00:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! I'm going to\Ncall you Phyllis!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.84,0:00:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[funny voice] Don't you\Nlook good, Phyllis.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.11,0:00:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,[same funny voice] Come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.22,0:00:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[cough]\N[normal voice]\NI mean, uh, come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.08,0:00:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, were you just\Ntalking to someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.65,0:00:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Why? Heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.42,0:00:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight, I have something very\Nimportant to discuss with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.72,0:00:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is about\Nleaving early yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.53,0:00:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have any\Nstudents on my schedule
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.36,0:00:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and Trixie was having\Na "magical emergency,"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.26,0:00:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which actually turned\Nout to be nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.63,0:00:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not anything\Nlike that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.74,0:00:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahem!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.60,0:00:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight Sparkle, the\NPrincess of Friendship,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.97,0:00:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in light of her\Nimpending ascension
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.51,0:00:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to the throne of Equestria\Nand in anticipation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.34,0:00:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of her many duties and\Nresponsibilities forthwith,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.38,0:00:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,does hereby intend\Nto make good
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.22,0:00:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,on her previous offer to\Nyou, Starlight Glimmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.45,0:00:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of replacing her as Headmare\Nof the School of Friendship!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.89,0:00:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to take over the\Nschool when I move to Canterlot.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.56,0:00:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I KNOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.59,0:01:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just so.. amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.93,0:01:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.00,0:01:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think I'm\Nreally up for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.53,0:01:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.43,0:01:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I've covered for you every\Ntime you've had to run off
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.30,0:01:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and save Equestria,\Nbut, I mean, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.27,0:01:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!\NThank You!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.67,0:01:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.84,0:01:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't think of any pony\Nwho'd be better for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.15,0:01:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a little nervous,\Nand excited,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.32,0:01:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm mostly just\Nnervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.55,0:01:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.65,0:01:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I'll have a lot of\Nimportant responsibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.92,0:01:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as ruler of Equestria, but\NI'll always be available
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.79,0:01:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to help whenever\Nyou need.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.89,0:01:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you supposed to be at\Na Royal Etiquette lesson
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.16,0:01:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with Celestia and\NLuna right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.73,0:01:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! Can't underestimate the\Nimportant responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.60,0:01:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of Royal napkin\Nplacement..!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.47,0:01:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.57,0:01:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, no biggie,\Nright Phyllis?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.14,0:01:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've totally got this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.62,0:02:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.42,0:02:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I'm nothing but\Nproud that you've been
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.26,0:02:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,officially offered the\Nposition of Headmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.79,0:02:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[tentatively] Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.99,0:02:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But, I can't\Nhelp wondering
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.09,0:02:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's going to cut into\Nour social schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.80,0:02:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.43,0:02:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Take now,\Nfor example.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.07,0:02:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of heading to the\Ndelightful lunch I had planned,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.14,0:02:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we're striding with\Ndetermination toward
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.54,0:02:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what I can only assume\Nis Twilight's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.28,0:02:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, our lunch\Nis super important,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.21,0:02:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but so is taking\Nover the school
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.15,0:03:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the only pony who's really\N{\i1}run{\i0} the School of Friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.88,0:03:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is the {\i1}Princess{\i0}\Nof Friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.15,0:03:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm worried about\Ndoing it all alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.05,0:03:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so I want to get as much\Nadvice from Twilight
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.29,0:03:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as I can while\Nshe's still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.82,0:03:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But Twilight's never\Nreally done anything alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.56,0:03:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She always has\Nher friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.03,0:03:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But that just\Ngave me an idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.70,0:03:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Trixie!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.77,0:03:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can give good advice\Nwhen you don't mean to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.97,0:03:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, thanks?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.74,0:03:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we still doing lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.11,0:03:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.34,0:03:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting Royal Place\NSettings just right
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.28,0:03:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is a lot harder\Nthan it looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.28,0:03:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, umm..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.12,0:03:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how busy you are, but\NI wanted to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.85,0:03:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about running the school\Nbecause, honestly,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.42,0:03:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a bit worried about\Ntaking it over all on my own,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.32,0:03:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just realized\NYOU never did it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.69,0:03:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a friend help\Nout {\i1}is{\i0} pretty great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.77,0:03:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think about me\Nhiring a {\i1}Vice{\i0}-Headmare
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:03:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to help run things?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.47,0:04:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust you to run the\Nschool any way you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.88,0:04:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that means\Nhiring a Vice-Headmare,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.01,0:04:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.78,0:04:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Really!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.78,0:04:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Like you said, I've always\Nhad ponies around to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.65,0:04:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't worry, you can\Nalways call on me to--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.72,0:04:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Twilight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.69,0:04:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarity says you were supposed\Nto be at the boutique
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.56,0:04:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,five minutes ago for your second\Nfitting for the coronation gown.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.39,0:04:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh. How many fittings are\Nthere going to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.39,0:04:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.76,0:04:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, good luck finding\Nyour Vice-Headmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.40,0:04:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you'll pick the\Nright pony for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.30,0:04:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. I heard the\Nwhole thing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.07,0:04:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and all I can say\Nis, I am humbled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.64,0:04:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.28,0:04:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I hadn't ever\Nconsidered it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.88,0:04:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but hearing you say it\Nout loud made me realize
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.91,0:04:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,what a great and powerful\NVice-Headmare I'll be!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.92,0:04:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, we get to work {\i1}and{\i0}\Nsocialize at the same time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.75,0:04:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Well, sure, that\Nwould be fun, but
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.06,0:04:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't just\N{\i1}give{\i0} you the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.12,0:04:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, no. Of\Ncourse not..
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.69,0:04:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine there's a lengthy\N"process" to go through
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.56,0:04:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,before you inevitably hire the\N"best pony" for the position.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.73,0:05:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Wink!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.80,0:05:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll probably\Ninterview several ponies..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.54,0:05:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.\N"Several." Wink.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.04,0:05:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you keep\Nsaying wink?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.31,0:05:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying wink!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.88,0:05:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Wink.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.35,0:05:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you all decided to\Nbe part of the search
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.89,0:05:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for the School of\NFriendship's Vice-Headmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.65,0:05:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, if you're looking\Nfor somepony to fundraise,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.86,0:05:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can bring in\Nenough bits
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.33,0:05:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to have several buildings\Nnamed after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.23,0:05:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's not the\N{\i1}primary{\i0} responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.03,0:05:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Vice-Headmare,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but anypony\Nis welcome to apply!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.97,0:05:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the selection\Nprocess I've come up with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.84,0:05:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is pretty special.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.71,0:05:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[loud whisper]\NAlbeit unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Wink!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.71,0:05:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.85,0:05:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you ALL have to prove\Nyou have what it takes to be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.35,0:05:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice-Headmare, I've designed\Nthe interview in three stages.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.59,0:05:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Each stage will test a different\Nskill the Vice-Headmare needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.12,0:05:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Only those who do WELL will\Nmove through the stages
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.96,0:06:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,until finally the best\Ncandidate rises to the top!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.76,0:06:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, without further ado,\Nit's time for stage one:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.53,0:06:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Substituting for\Nthe teachers!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.84,0:06:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the students\Nget a sample
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of my great and\Npowerful instruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.08,0:06:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they might not\Nwant to go back
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.64,0:06:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to the regular\Nfaculty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.08,0:06:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.42,0:06:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that seam\Nis so straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.82,0:06:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You really learned how to sew\Nfrom mending apple sacks
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.06,0:06:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,on the farm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.99,0:06:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeyup.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, loyalty\Nis the foundation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.90,0:06:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of friendship and trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.43,0:06:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But nothing gets more loyalty\Nthan a big stack of bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.77,0:06:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This book on business will teach\Nyou all how to earn your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.27,0:06:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter one: Equity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.25,0:06:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [orchestral music] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.02,0:07:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [out-of-tune blast] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.56,0:07:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [walking jazz bass] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.79,0:07:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.03,0:07:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.00,0:07:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahhhh!\N[bird chirps]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.11,0:07:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Pre-Equestria Era, year\N1322, Abraxius the Bold did...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.18,0:07:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,ooh a bunch of boring stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.05,0:07:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for a {\i1}really{\i0} long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.12,0:07:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, I know history's important,\Nbut I never learned any of it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.46,0:07:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and look how {\i1}I{\i0} turned out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.77,0:07:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Wink.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.48,0:07:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.34,0:08:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, Phyllis, obviously\Nthose three are moving on..
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.85,0:08:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.25,0:08:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmhm. I think we're in\Nagreement on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.52,0:08:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[groan] I know what you're\Ngoing to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.16,0:08:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But it would be SO much fun\Nto have my Vice-Headmare
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.13,0:08:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,be a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.80,0:08:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She just needs a little\Nmore hoof-holding
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.67,0:08:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,than some of the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.83,0:08:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but it could still\Nwork out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.70,0:08:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight, I've given\Nthis a lot of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.31,0:08:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and even though I\Nstill believe naps
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.98,0:08:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,are a valid use\Nof class time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.81,0:08:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be the one\Nrunning the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.48,0:08:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you say no\Nnaps, then no naps!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.38,0:08:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know I can be\Na little stubborn
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.68,0:08:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the\Nbest listener,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.95,0:08:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just can't\NWAIT for us to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.62,0:08:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,tackle this job\Nas a team!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.22,0:08:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Two great and powerful\Nfriends taking on the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.16,0:08:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know you still have\Nto go through all this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.63,0:08:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"interview" stuff, wink,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.16,0:08:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just had to tell\Nyou how excited I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.50,0:08:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,See? I told you\Nit could work...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.47,0:09:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.71,0:09:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, remaining\NVice-Headmare candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.22,0:09:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Stage Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.85,0:09:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you are here because\Nyou performed well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.72,0:09:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or.. {\i1}well enough{\i0}, to face\Nyour next challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.62,0:09:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Parent-Teacher conferences!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.73,0:09:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vice-Headmare will need to\Nbe a master communicator
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.73,0:09:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can't think of a\Nbetter test of that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.83,0:09:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,than meeting with our students\Nand their parents or guardians.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.60,0:09:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I eagerly look forward to\Nsharing my love of science
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.61,0:09:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with both progeny\Nand progenitors!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.51,0:09:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.71,0:09:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,An orchestra is made up of\Ndifferent parts
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.01,0:09:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and good communication\Nis the key to harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.35,0:09:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeyup!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.68,0:09:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A lifetime on stage has taught\Nme that good communication
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.92,0:09:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is essential to holding your\Naudience's attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.19,0:09:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which is why Trixie\Nis also known
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.89,0:09:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as a great and\Npowerful communicator!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.23,0:10:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Life at the School of\NFriendship is like a song,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.90,0:10:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and although she started out\Nsinging her part pianissimo,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.34,0:10:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ocellus is now\Nsoloing fortissimo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.71,0:10:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh. Indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.05,0:10:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The science curriculum at this\Nschool is somewhat lacking,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.38,0:10:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but Yona has taken to the\Nsubject like a yak to smashing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.75,0:10:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If fostered, I believe she\Ncould easily blaze a trail
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.66,0:10:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and expand our understanding\Nof science itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,YAKS BEST! YAKS BEST! YAKS BEST!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.63,0:10:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Gallus is a\Nfantastic student.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.50,0:10:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He's even taught me a\Nthing or two about napping!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.20,0:10:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[yawn] Is that why you're\Nputting ME to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.14,0:10:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.64,0:10:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why I have\Nto come to these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.65,0:10:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, most parents or guardians\NWANT to be involved
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.68,0:10:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in our students' lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.22,0:10:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should find a\N{\i1}different{\i0} representative
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.89,0:10:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from Griffonstone to\Nbe Gallus' guardian!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.56,0:10:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that'd be great!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:11:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you find one,\NLET ME KNOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.06,0:11:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so CONFUSED!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.43,0:11:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying\NSilverstream is exuberant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeyup.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.70,0:11:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And enthusiastic?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.30,0:11:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeyup..
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.57,0:11:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But aren't\Nthose the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.77,0:11:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And are they good?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.81,0:11:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you could be trying\Nto tell me she's unfocused,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.54,0:11:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but then you might\Njust be explaining
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.61,0:11:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that you appreciate\Nher high energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.41,0:11:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. Nope, Eeyup, er...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.95,0:11:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.02,0:11:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There seems to be a lot of\Nnuance here and I just want to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.82,0:11:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure I understand\Nexactly what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.96,0:11:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So what are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.46,0:11:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhhhhhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.96,0:11:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Gallus doesn't need to\Nknow I'm "proud" of him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.13,0:11:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And he certainly\Ndoesn't need me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.87,0:11:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,trekking all the\Nway to Ponyville!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.70,0:11:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Good! Because you're\Nno longer WELCOME!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.57,0:11:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Well fine\Nwith me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.31,0:11:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Trixie, what\Nhappened!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.61,0:11:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure, but we'll\Nhave one less conference
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.48,0:11:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to worry about\Nnext semester.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.15,0:12:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate\Nyour honesty, Big Mac,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.39,0:12:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.42,0:12:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Parents expect a lot of\Ndetailed communication
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.86,0:12:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes\Nto their kids
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.33,0:12:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you aren't\Ncomfortable with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.06,0:12:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice-Headmare probably\Nisn't the job for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.83,0:12:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.36,0:12:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.17,0:12:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight, I know why\Nyou wanted to see me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.41,0:12:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't\Nhave to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.14,0:12:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.44,0:12:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's thoughtful that you'd\Nwant to check in on me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.64,0:12:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,after my shocking confrontation\Nwith Grandpa Gruff,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.91,0:12:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but never fear.\NI shall recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.62,0:12:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Trixie, that's not exactly what\NI wanted to talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.15,0:12:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get into a\Nshouting match with parents!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.86,0:12:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Or guardians.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.22,0:12:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For the final stage of\Nthe interview process,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.26,0:12:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll each have to put\Ntogether a field trip
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.46,0:12:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you really\NDO want the job,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.50,0:12:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I need yours to\Nbe exceptional
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.93,0:12:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because if I had to pick a\NVice-Headmare right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it wouldn't be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.37,0:12:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see what\Nyou're doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.97,0:12:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, you're not going to\Ngive the job to somepony else,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.44,0:12:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but you want to see my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.51,0:13:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, message received!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.25,0:13:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wink.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.02,0:13:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, Trixie, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.62,0:13:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The Great and Powerful Trixie is\Nabout to pull out all the stops!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.19,0:13:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you're ready for the\Nmost exceptional field trip
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.03,0:13:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to ever grace this school!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.73,0:13:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it wrong for me to think\Nshe might actually pull it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.84,0:13:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.38,0:13:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Not looking forward\Nto the performance?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.28,0:13:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Octavia\Nloves music,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.35,0:13:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but a field trip to a\Nclassical music performance
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.82,0:13:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't my idea of\Nan exciting time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.59,0:13:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [loud synthesizer{\i0}\N{\i1} accompaniment] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.32,0:13:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.07,0:13:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. I take it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.17,0:14:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard we'd be\Narranging field trips,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew right away I wanted\Nto take you all to my lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.68,0:14:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I can think of\Nno better trip
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.21,0:14:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,than one through\Nthe quantum field!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.15,0:14:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I am referring to\Ntime travel!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.22,0:14:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been working on a\Ntemporal transportation device!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.73,0:14:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.96,0:14:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And 3, 4, 5..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.87,0:14:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.20,0:14:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You are now five\Nseconds into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.60,0:14:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You see we are all\Nalready time travelers!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.07,0:14:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.48,0:14:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.61,0:14:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. I hadn't actually thought\Nthat much beyond.. this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.39,0:14:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ponies and other students!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.56,0:14:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the greatest and\Nmost powerful field trip
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.73,0:14:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of your lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.56,0:14:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Where Yona and\Nfriends going?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.40,0:14:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I am thrilled you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.23,0:15:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Because today we're not doing a\Nnormal, old, {\i1}boring{\i0} field trip,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.47,0:15:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,where you GO somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.54,0:15:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So.. not field trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.74,0:15:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Au contraire.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.04,0:15:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have easily taken\Nyou to Froggy Bottom Bog.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.65,0:15:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't need to leave\Nthe comfort of the classroom
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.92,0:15:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for our field trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.45,0:15:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I{\i0} can bring the\Nfield trip to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.85,0:15:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [action music] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.63,0:15:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Trixie! What did you do!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.97,0:15:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I found the perfect\Nlittle patch of bog
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.20,0:15:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to teleport into\Nthe school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.37,0:15:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I just didn't\Nconsider the possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.58,0:15:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that a hive of flash bees\Nmight have nested there..
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.60,0:15:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.13,0:16:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Who told you bees to nest in\Nmy patch of field trip bog!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.23,0:16:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Trixie, go with\Nthe students.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.47,0:16:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll handle\Nthis!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.47,0:16:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I was only trying\Nto give them
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,an exceptional field\Ntrip experience
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.31,0:16:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which you have\Nto admit I did!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.14,0:16:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Woah!\NWe'll talk about\Nit later!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.84,0:16:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.02,0:16:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Starlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.95,0:16:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.06,0:16:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So um...\Nthey're gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.99,0:16:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes{\i0}..
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.19,0:16:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice. Teamwork.\NAm I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.86,0:16:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.03,0:16:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what team\N{\i1}you're{\i0} on, but it isn't mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.67,0:16:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was DANGEROUS!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.12,0:16:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the words you're looking\Nfor are "great and powerful".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.07,0:16:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,IT WASN'T EVEN ACCEPTABLE!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.28,0:16:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You went from not taking it\Nseriously to blowing things
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.11,0:16:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,so out of proportion, you put\Nevery creature in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.05,0:16:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to work\Nwith a friend SO much,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.52,0:16:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I ignored the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.65,0:17:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would NEVER\Nbe right for the job!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.85,0:17:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm confused. What\Nare you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.76,0:17:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying you'll\NNEVER be Vice-Headmare!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.96,0:17:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But, but, I thought you\Ncreated the position for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.30,0:17:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,WHY WOULD YOU THINK THAT?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.67,0:17:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I created the position\Nbecause I need HELP,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.60,0:17:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can't think of any way\Nthat you would ever help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.34,0:17:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But Twilight's friends\Nalways helped her..
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.81,0:17:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's because Twilight's\Nfriends are competent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.81,0:17:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They care about\Nwhat they're doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.65,0:17:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,AND they know how\Nto do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.95,0:17:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess I won't take\Nup any more of your time,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.79,0:17:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmare Starlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.02,0:17:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.66,0:17:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.83,0:17:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought I'd check\Nin to see how the search
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,for a Vice-Headmare\Nwas going.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.40,0:17:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.10,0:17:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,OK...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.47,0:17:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wanted\Nit to be a friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.47,0:17:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so I ended up pushing aside\Nsome pretty big signs
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.21,0:17:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that it wasn't\Ngonna work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.14,0:17:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everypony is\Nright for every job,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.58,0:18:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but everypony has\Nsomething to contribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.28,0:18:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The trick is\Nfiguring out what.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.08,0:18:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you and your\Nfriend can't figure it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.75,0:18:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a job to do, you\Nhave to decide what's best
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.86,0:18:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and be upfront and honest,\Neven if that means
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.09,0:18:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't work with\Na friend on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.23,0:18:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I guess that means talking\Nto them at the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of stringing them along\Nuntil you get so frustrated
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you totally lose it and say a\Nbunch of really awful things?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.51,0:18:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Trixie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.08,0:18:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.85,0:18:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.52,0:18:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for all\Nthose things I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.15,0:18:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I just really wanted\Nit to work out,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.69,0:18:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,even though I knew\Nit probably wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.63,0:18:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have said\Nsomething sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.46,0:18:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, we can't\Nhave what we want
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.73,0:18:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'm TERRIBLE\Nat everything
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.20,0:18:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and could never\Nhelp you with anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.30,0:18:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You aren't terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.00,0:18:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have a lot\Nof great qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.34,0:19:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe not Vice-Headmare\Nqualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.91,0:19:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but great and powerful\Nfriend qualities...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.05,0:19:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you really stand by\Nthe ponies you care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.45,0:19:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Gallus even said no creatures\NEVER stuck up for him
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.35,0:19:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you did\Nwith Grandpa Gruff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.06,0:19:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have been nice to\Nrun the school together,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.36,0:19:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but not everypony is\Nright for every job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.06,0:19:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how you take your\Nresponsibilities seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.50,0:19:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe I should have known\NI wasn't exactly a perfect fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.44,0:19:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If it makes you feel\Nany better, nopony was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.51,0:19:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.61,0:19:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Dr. Hooves has decided to\Ngo back to his experiments
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.18,0:19:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and Octavia is worried the\Nresponsibilities of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.45,0:19:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice-Headmare will take too\Nmuch time away from her music.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe getting a Vice-Headmare\Nwas a bad idea..
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.96,0:19:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.89,0:19:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, you'd like some help,\Nand hiring a Vice-Headmare
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.93,0:19:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,IS a great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.83,0:19:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But.. who could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.66,0:20:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you need somepony\Nwho's responsible like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.57,0:20:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and detail-oriented,\Nlike Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.34,0:20:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And smart, obviously, it\Nis a school after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.74,0:20:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be nice if I\Ngot along with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.91,0:20:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,since having it be a\Nfriend can't work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.18,0:20:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it can!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.52,0:20:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...and I knew as soon as\NI read Trixie's scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.22,0:20:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was the exact right\Nthing for me to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.86,0:20:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about being\NFlurry Heart's Crystaler?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.43,0:20:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, honestly, now that\NFlurry Heart's a little older,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.16,0:20:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there really isn't\Nmuch for me to do
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.80,0:20:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of the occasional\Ntradition or festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.23,0:20:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And working at a school is what\NI always thought I'd do,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.30,0:20:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you'll have me..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.24,0:20:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.71,0:20:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're hired!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.81,0:20:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a feeling\Nthis would work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.71,0:20:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Trixie, thank\Nyou so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.35,0:20:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Between being insightful\Nwhen I want to be
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.55,0:20:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and giving good advice\Nwhen I don't mean to,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose I can be a\Npretty good friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.62,0:20:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,More than that, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.26,0:20:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You really did\Ngive good advice,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.26,0:20:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you helped me talk\Nthrough the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.03,0:21:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of finding the right\Npony for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.99,0:21:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know you care\Nabout the students..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.20,0:21:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Trixie the Great and\NPowerful Advice Giver,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.43,0:21:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Problem Talk Througher,\Nand Student Care Abouter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.84,0:21:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh. I think I'll go\Nwith friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.80,0:21:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend is perfect, but.. there's a\Nposition here at the school
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.14,0:21:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you might be\Nright for too..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.31,0:21:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you say to being\Nthe School of Friendship's
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.65,0:21:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,NEW student counselor?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.45,0:21:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, this office needs\Na bit of redecorating!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.69,0:21:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Potted plants\Nscream desperation..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Phyllis! No!
